Originally Answered: How long do American football games usually last?

The regulation clock playing time is 4 - 15 minute quarters totaling one hour.

But the clock stops between some plays (first down, incomplete pass, time outs, penalties etc. ) changeover and a break for halftime and some other things like injuries, and reviews.

So the entire game elapsed time in college and professional football can be expected to take close to three and a half hours. If overtime happens (tie game in regulation time) then various overtime schemes can add additional time to a sudden death format.

An NFL game typically lasts about three hours. The game is divided into four quarters, each lasting 15 minutes, but the actual time can extend due to stoppages for timeouts, halftime (which is 12 minutes), and other delays such as penalties, injuries, and commercial breaks. The clock often stops for various reasons, so the total viewing time is usually significantly longer than the actual game time.

Originally Answered: How long do American football games usually last?

As others have stated, the NFL and college play four 15 min. quarters. Most high schools play four 12 min quarters. As a general rule, NFL and college games last a little over 3 hours and a high school game usually around 2 1/2 hours. A lot of variables can go into this, especially in high school. How many running plays vs. passing plays, number of first downs, how many time the player goes out of bounds, does the game go to overtime, does each team take their allotted time outs each half. All of this can lengthen or shorten a game.

An NFL game has four 15-minute quarters, though there are many stoppages in play and stopping of the game clock, for numerous reasons. In between the second and third quarter is a halftime break, during which the teams retreat to their locker rooms to regroup and plan for the next half of the game.

Originally Answered: How long do American football games usually last?

Clocked at only an hour, the average game lasts a little more than three hours. While the ball is in play for only 60 minutes, theres twice as much down time due to:

  • Huddles
  • Time outs
  • Injury time outs
  • Penalty enforcement
  • Replay reviews
  • Half time break
  • Break between quarters
  • Official time outs

To name a few interruptions.

Originally Answered: How long is a typical NFL game?

As a rule, the scheduled 60 minutes of game time actually occupy between 3 and 3 1/4 hours, depending on the number of injury stoppages, TV timeouts, replay challenges/reviews etc. If overtime is required, then this can be extended by up to 30 minutes (and even more in the post-season, where overtime continues until one team wins regardless of the time required).

Originally Answered: How long does the American football game last?

Football games last for a total of 60 minutes in professional and college play, and are divided into two halves of 30 minutes and four quarters of 15 minutes.

Games last longer, than their defined length, due to play stoppages - the average NFL game lasts slightly over 3 hours.
